Sentencas: A long term durability test is conducted on a large area 10 x 10 cm(2) metal-supported cell.
Titulo: Performance and long term durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell that consists of a porous nickel-iron substrate as a support, an La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5-Mn0.5O3-delta (LSCM) interlayer, a nano-structured Ce0.55La0.45O2-delta (LDC)-Ni anode, an LDC isolation layer, an La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte, a Sm0.15Ce0.85O3-delta (SDC) barrier layer and a SDC-Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC) cathode is prepared by using an atmospheric plasma spraying technology.
Titulo: Performance and long term durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The measured maximum output powers are 40.4, 31.2 and 22.7 W at 750, 700 and 650 degrees C respectively.
Titulo: Performance and long term durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the long term durability test, the cell voltages are measured in a constant current mode (400 mA cm(-2)) for 3000 h at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Performance and long term durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The measured I-V curves and AC impedance data are used to trace the variations of ohmic and non-ohmic resistances at different times.
Titulo: Performance and long term durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is found that the dominant factors in the degradation of the tested cell are the increases of activation polarization and ohmic resistances.
Titulo: Performance and long term durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The tested cell is heat treated at the condition of 820 degrees C and OCV for 4 h after 500 h durability test, the measured I-V curves and cell voltages show that the tested cell is recovered and demonstrate that the heat treated process at the condition of 820 degrees C and OCV for 4 h is effective to recover the performance of the prepared cell.
Titulo: Performance and long term durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Based on the measured experimental data and the post microstructure analysis, the degradation of the tested cell is mainly due to the microstructural change in the anode and micro-cracks formed at layer interfaces that have significant thermal expansion mismatches, they cause the increases of activation polarization and ohmic resistances.
Titulo: Performance and long term durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After the recovery process, it is found the ohmic resistance decreases.
Titulo: Performance and long term durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells
